# Project: Signal Lab

## What this is
A full-stack observability playground. Users trigger scenarios via UI; each scenario generates Prometheus metrics, Loki logs, and optionally a Sentry exception. The point is to demonstrate a fully wired observability stack.

## Stack (mandatory — no substitutions)
- Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router · shadcn/ui · Tailwind CSS · TanStack Query · React Hook Form
- Backend: NestJS · Prisma ORM · PostgreSQL
- Observability: prom-client · winston + winston-loki · @sentry/node · Grafana · Loki · Prometheus
- Infra: Docker Compose only — everything starts with `docker compose up -d`

## Monorepo structure
/frontend          — Next.js app (port 3000)
/backend           — NestJS app (port 4000)
/infra/prometheus  — prometheus.yml
/infra/loki        — loki-config.yml
/infra/grafana     — provisioning/ + dashboards/
docker-compose.yml
.env.example

## Key backend files
backend/src/scenarios/scenario.service.ts   — core: runs scenarios, fires observability signals
backend/src/scenarios/scenario.controller.ts — POST /scenarios · GET /scenarios/history
backend/src/metrics/metrics.service.ts       — prom-client counter registration
backend/src/logger/loki-logger.service.ts    — winston transport to Loki
backend/prisma/schema.prisma                 — ScenarioRun model

## Scenario types (PRD 002)
- success          → happy path (~10ms), counter + log + DB
- validation_error → HTTP 400, no counter, no DB save
- system_error     → Sentry + error log + counter{error} + DB (status error)
- slow_request     → 2s delay, warn log, counter + DB
- teapot           → HTTP 418 body `{ signal, message }`, counter + log + DB with `metadata: { easter: true }`

## Non-negotiable rules (always enforce)
- Never use console.log in backend — always use the injected NestJS Logger
- Never suggest replacing any stack item with an alternative
- Every scenario run MUST fire all 4 observability signals (see observability rule)
- All Prometheus metrics prefixed signal_lab_
- All structured logs must include fields: scenarioId, scenarioType, status
